events.description: The Reserve Bank raised its cash rate for the first time in two years.
Data showing Australia’s services sector posting its strongest expansion in nearly four years.
Upcoming trade balance figures providing clues on the economy’s health.

facts.fact_text: The Australian dollar strengthened to approximately $0.703 on Wednesday.

evidences.evidence_text: The Australian dollar strengthened further to around $0.703 on Wednesday

facts.fact_text: The Reserve Bank of Australia implemented its first rate hike in two years during the February meeting.

facts.fact_text: Australia's services sector expansion reached a nearly four-year high.
